The Inter-Ministerial Task Team on the Nigeria tragedy led by Minister Jeff Radebe will brief the media on the developments regarding the 11 outstanding mortal remains that were still being identified by the Nigerian government. This is part of government s commitment to keep the South African public abreast on the situation. Members of the media are invited as follows: Date: Sunday 1st February 2015 Time: 10h00 Venue: GCIS Head Office, Tshedimosetso House, 1035 Francis Baard Street, Hatfield, Pretoria NB: There will be a video-link to Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Parliament, Cape Town. RSVP: Themba Thobela (Pretoria) Cell: 076 09 56555 E-mail: Thembat@doc.gov.zaMzimasi Ngqelu (Cape Town) Cell: 076 904 3557 E-mail: Mzi@doc.gov.za Enquiries: Phumla Williams Spokesperson for the Inter-Ministerial Task Team on Nigeria Tragedy Cell: 083 501 0139Issued by Department of Communications (DoC) on behalf of the Inter- Ministerial Task Team on the Nigeria tragedy